        "title": "refactor: extract normalization core package",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Extract shared normalization/coercion helpers into private workspace package `@openclaw/normalization-core` with built dist artifacts.\n- Rewrite core, UI, tooling, and package build imports to use the new package boundary while preserving existing `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*-runtime` public SDK subpaths.\n- Keep the new package name out of extension package-boundary aliases and emitted plugin SDK declarations, and wire UI/test resolvers for browser-safe imports.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs packages/normalization-core/src src/plugins/sdk-alias.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/extension-package-project-boundaries.test.ts test/scripts/dev-tooling-safety.test.ts test/plugin-npm-release.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm --filter @openclaw/normalization-core build`\n- `pnpm build:plugin-sdk:dts && node --experimental-strip-types scripts/write-plugin-sdk-entry-dts.ts && rg -n \"@openclaw/normalization-core\" dist/plugin-sdk packages/plugin-sdk/dist || true`\n- `node scripts/build-all.mjs cliStartup`\n- `pnpm check:import-cycles`\n- `node scripts/check-package-dist-imports.mjs .`\n- `pnpm --dir ui build`\n- `pnpm --dir ui test src/ui/chat/slash-commands.browser-import.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` clean after two accepted findings were fixed\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: shared number/string/record normalization helpers now live in `@openclaw/normalization-core` while existing plugin SDK helper subpaths remain the public plugin API.\nReal environment tested: local macOS checkout, Node/pnpm repo toolchain, UI Vite build, plugin SDK declaration generation, changed gate.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `pnpm check:changed`; `pnpm --dir ui build`; `pnpm --dir ui test src/ui/chat/slash-commands.browser-import.test.ts`; `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`.\nEvidence after fix: changed gate passed; UI build passed; UI targeted test passed; final autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\nObserved result after fix: package/runtime declarations no longer leak direct `@openclaw/normalization-core` imports through plugin SDK outputs, UI resolves the new package, and import cycles remain clean.\nWhat was not tested: live gateway/provider flows; this is an internal package-boundary refactor with behavior-preserving moved tests.\n",
